Session create and update are synchronous reread
flows. OCI returns the body immediately and the
model exposes no lifecycle or work-request
surface, so the reviewed runtime settles Active
after a confirmed reread.
The published runtime keeps path identity
explicit: agentEndpointId is required from spec,
sessionId is learned from the OCI body, and
status records both values for reread, update,
and delete addressing.
No ListSessions API exists in the pinned SDK, so
the controller does not publish list-based
pre-create reuse or delete-confirmation fallback
semantics.
Delete confirmation relies on GetSession
returning NotFound after DeleteSession because
delete responses carry headers only.
end note
